{{Infobox non-profit |name =Athar Blood Bank |image =Athar Blood Bank logo.jpg |type =[[Blood Bank]] |founded_date =02 June 2012 |founder =[[Syed Shahabuddin Salfi Firdausi]] |location =1st Floor, Jamiya complex, Near Samachar Chowk, [[Solapur]], [[Maharashtra]]-413002 |area_served =[[Maharashtra]] |focus =Voluntary Blood Donations |method =Camp |key_people =Syed Shahabuddin Salfi Firdausi, Mushtaq Chaudhary, Abdul Razzaq Kamble, Azam Shaikh, Dr. Nilofer Bohri, Usman Mansoori, Qayyum Inamdar, Mukhtar Humnabadi |motto =Service to Humanity}}
Athar Blood Bank is an initiative by '''Athar Minorities Social and Welfare Association''' and is based in Solapur, Maharashtra.<ref>http://www.cdsco.nic.in/writereaddata/BLOOD%20BANKS%20INDIAfeb2015.pdf</ref> The Athar Blood Bank was inaugurated on 2nd June 2012 by Mr. [[Sushil Kumar Shinde]] (then [[Ministry of Power (India)|Minister of Power (India))]]. ''Service to Humanity'' was the slogan chosen by the founder as a motto for Athar Blood Bank. Construction of new Maternity Home is on cards of the Athar Minorities Social and Welfare Association in near future. It is running successfully and conducts blood donation camps across state and helping the humanity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tajallieshahabblog.wordpress.com/in-news/|title=News|date=14 January 2016|publisher=}}</ref> [[File:Athar Blood Bank Solapur (Inauguration).jpg|thumb|Athar Blood Bank Inauguration ceremony. (L-R) Maulana Syed Shahabuddin Salfi Firdausi and Sushil Kumar Shinde (Then Minister of Power India)]] [[File:Athar Blood Bank (Inaugration).jpg|thumb|Athar Blood Bank Inauguration ceremony. (L-R) Alka Rathod, Praniti Shinde, Maulana Syed Shahabuddin Salfi Firdausi, Sushil Kumar Shinde, Dilip Rao Mane, Qayyum Inamdar]] ==Background== Athar Blood Bank was established in 2012 by [[Syed Shahabuddin Salfi Firdausi|Maulana Syed Shahabuddin Salfi Firdausi]] who is renowned Islamic scholar, Author and Peace Activist.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mumbai/report-muslim-scholars-support-ban-on-triple-talaq-polygamy-2433070|title=Muslim scholars support ban on triple talaq, polygamy {{!}} Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=2017-05-10|work=dna|access-date=2017-05-11|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://twocircles.net/2017may26/410093.html|title=Maulana Syed Shahabuddin Salfi Firdausi: A cleric who built a Blood Bank in Solapur {{!}} TwoCircles.net|last=TwoCircles.net|website=twocircles.net|language=en-US|access-date=2017-06-06}}</ref>
==Blood Collection Center== Blood collection center at 1st Floor, Jamiya complex, Near Samachar Chowk, [[Solapur]], [[Maharashtra]] is equipped with all the latest equipment and can host multiple blood donations simultaneously.<ref>{{Google maps|url=https://goo.gl/maps/vcdxaBjTGZR2|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref> Eighteen staff, including 3 M.D. doctors work at the center and has capacity to store 700 units. It is operational 24*7 and supplies blood to Government Civil Hospital and Private Hospitals across Solapur district. Bank provides free blood to Thalassemia and HIV patient. Also financially weak sections are given discounted rate and sometimes they are not charged at all<ref name=":0" /> <gallery> Athar Blood Bank 3.png|Athar Blood Bank (Exterior) Athar Blood Bank (Interior).jpg|Athar Blood Bank (Interior) </gallery>
==Camp== Athar Blood Bank collects blood from different groups e.g. [[Colleges]] and [[Public]] or Private Organizations, where any person can donate blood. Bank organizes an average of seven blood donation camps in a month. Blood is transported through an ambulance which also provides mobile [[medical facility]].
Recently 200 people have donated the blood in a camp organized by Jamiat-e-Ahle Hadeeths in Social School, Solapur. <ref>{{cite news | author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date = 2017-04-06| title = 'Social' madhya 200 janacha raktdaan |trans-title =200 people donated in blood donation camp held in "Social School" | url =http://epaper.lokmat.com/sub-editions/Hello%20Solapur/2017-04-06/4 | language = Marathi| work =Lokmat | location =Solapur | access-date =2017-04-07 }}</ref>
==Processing of Blood== The blood is processed in the lab having state-of-art facility after the collection either from center or camps. After initial screening blood gets separated in major three components e.g. Red cells, Plasma and Platelets.
