'''Covenant Health''' is largest Catholic health care provider in [[Canada]]. It was established on October 7, 2008, by Patrick Dumelie, following the amalgamation of [[Alberta|Alberta's]] regional Catholic health care providers under a single administration.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wcr.ab.ca/news/2009/0223/health022309.shtml|author=Western Catholic Reporter|title=Figures at a Glance|accessdate=2009-05-11}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>
The organization is governed by a board of directors consists of 11 individuals, who are appointed by, and accountable to, the Catholic Bishops of Alberta,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.covenanthealth.ca/about-us/board-of-directors.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-01-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116132438/http://www.covenanthealth.ca/about-us/board-of-directors.html |archivedate=2014-01-16 |df= }}</ref> which itself includes 5 Latin bishops and 1 Ukrainian Catholic bishop.<ref>http://www.cccb.ca/site/eng/media-room/archives/media-releases/1998/663-alberta-bishops-statement-on-the-care-of-gods-creation</ref>
Covenant Health employs over 14,000 staff, physicians and volunteers in 16 facilities in 11 communities across Alberta in cooperation with [[Alberta Health Services]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.covenanthealth.ca/about-us/figures-at-a-glance.html |author=Covenant Health |title=Figures at a Glance |accessdate=2009-05-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090217103424/http://covenanthealth.ca/about-us/figures-at-a-glance.html |archivedate=2009-02-17 |df= }}</ref> Services provided include [[acute care]], [[continuing care]], [[assisted living]], [[hospice]], rehabilitation and [[respite care]], and seniors' housing.
