'''Lab Tests Online''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] non-profit web resource about [[Medical laboratory|clinical laboratory testing]].<ref name=ClinChemActa2014>{{cite journal | last1 = Campbell | first1 = B | last2 = Linzer | first2 = G | last3 = Dufour | first3 = DR | date = May 2014 | title = Lab Tests Online and consumer understanding of laboratory testing | url = | journal = Clin Chim Acta | volume = 432 | issue = | pages = 162–5 | doi = 10.1016/j.cca.2013.09.028 | pmid = 24121032 }}</ref><ref name=CLP10>{{cite news|last1=Linzer|first1=George|title=Lab Tests Online at 10 Years: 100 Million Served|url=http://www.clpmag.com/2011/07/lab-tests-online-at-10-years-100-million-served/|work=Clinical Lab Products|agency=Clinical Lab Products|publisher=Clinical Lab Products|date=July 5, 2011}}</ref> The site provides information on [[Medical test|clinical lab tests]] as well as conditions that are managed or diagnosed by [[Diagnostic test|lab tests]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kulkarni|first1=Shweta|title=Lab Tests Online Honoured With 2012 Communicator Award|url=http://www.medtecheurope.org/mediaroom/99/37/Lab-Tests-Online-Honoured-with-2012-Communicator-Award?cntnt01template=detail|accessdate=8 February 2015|publisher=Medtech Europe|date=13 July 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150208225922/http://www.medtecheurope.org/mediaroom/99/37/Lab-Tests-Online-Honoured-with-2012-Communicator-Award?cntnt01template=detail|archivedate=8 February 2015|df=}}</ref> Lab Tests Online also provides summaries of recommendations by age, feature articles on lab-related topics, and news items of patient interest.<ref>{{cite book|title=An Overview of Lab Tests Online|publisher=Clinical Laboratory Improvement Advisory Committee|page=6|url=ftp://ftp.cdc.gov/pub/CLIAC_meeting_presentations/pdf/Addenda/cliac0903/Q_LabTestsOnline.pdf|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref> All contents are reviewed and approved by an [[Editorial board|Editorial Review Board]] composed of [[Medical laboratory scientist|laboratory professionals]] before being posted to the site.<ref name=ClinChemActa2014/>
The site was launched in 2001 by the [[American Association for Clinical Chemistry]], the [[Learned society|scientific society]] for [[Clinical pathology|clinical laboratory science]] and is a collaboration with other professional societies representing the [[Clinical Chemistry and Laboratory Medicine|laboratory medicine]] community.<ref name=CLP10/><ref>{{cite book|last1=Chisolm|first1=Stephanie|title=The Health Professions: Trends and Opportunities in U.S. Health Care|date=Jul 3, 2008|publisher=Jones & Bartlett Publishers|isbn=0763735205|page=116|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DoTLPQHob1UC&pg=PA116}}</ref> The website is [[Mirror website|mirrored]] on other sites in other countries and is available via [[mobile app]]s in several countries.<ref name=AAAClto>{{cite web|title=Lab Tests Online|url=https://www.aacc.org/global-health-outreach/lab-tests-online|publisher=American Association for Clinical Chemistry|accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref>
